 MBOMBELA – Condolences are streaming in from all over the country mourning the death of the iconic photographer. Nzima took the legendary photo capturing Hector Peterson’s death during the Soweto uprising in 1976. The Department of Culture, Sport and Recreation confirmed Nzima’s death and gave credit to him saying: “The camera was his weapon of choice and he used it to expose the injustices of the previous regime.  READ ALSO: Historic icon celebrated and immortalised Lowvelder had the privilege to do interviews with Nzima and would like to extend our deepest condolences to his friends and family. See below some of the responses on social media mourning the loss of a legend in the industry.           